divs: sighting detailswe were on our way from scranton to philly to visit our son. it was a sunday, either may 23 or may 30. we were on rt. 476, n.e. turnpike ext. a short distance before getting on the schuylkill express way. as we were descending from high ground (my wife was driving)i caught a glimpse of what appeared to be a balloon (blimp). i say this because the rear end of the craft had thick fins very reminiscent of a blimp but the front was not. the front had an obvious nipple like protrusion jutting out and the top front had the same protrusion jutting upward 90 degrees to the protrusion at the tip. the body of the craft seemed to taper towards the rear end. it was grayish beige in color and seemed very low to the ground. it was impossible for this object not to be seen by numerous people in the area. could anyone from the philly area please tell me what this object was\is? *(wit's email address deleted--sgonzalez\cms).
